title: Oil kicks off week with gains on fresh hopes for U.S.-China trade talks
text: Oil prices began the week on a brighter note on Monday, posting early gains as positive noises from Washington over the weekend rekindled optimism in global markets that the United States and China could soon sign a deal to end their bitter trade war.

title: No 'phase two' U.S.-China deal on the horizon, officials say
text: An ambitious "phase two" trade deal between the United States and China is looking less likely as the two countries struggle to strike a preliminary "phase one" agreement, according to U.S. and Beijing officials, lawmakers and trade experts.
